how I can understand that we have integrated Appsflyer events, and it's track on Newsbreak

To ensure that you have integrated AppsFlyer events and they are being tracked on NewsBreak, follow these steps:
1. **Get Tracking URLs**: Go to 'Integrated Partners' on AppsFlyer and search for NewsBreak. Select 'Attribution Link' under 'NewsBreak' and retrieve your tracking URLs.
2. **Configure In-App Events**: Enable the in-app event postbacks and use NewsBreak event_type for mapping. Make sure to include values & revenue on AppsFlyer if you toggle on the Event value.
3. **Check Conversion Data**: For iOS, deactivate the advanced policy to ensure NewsBreak can receive all conversion data.
For more detailed instructions, you can refer to this article: [Introduction to App Install Events](https://help.newsbreak.com/hc/en-us/articles/26530008151309-Introduction-to-App-Install-Events).
I did this, and don`t have any installs on campaigns, how can I check that you receive data from our application

If you have followed the steps and still don't see any installs on your campaigns, you can check if NewsBreak is receiving data from your application by doing the following:
1. **Verify Tracking URLs**: Ensure that the tracking URLs are correctly implemented in your app and that they match the ones provided by AppsFlyer.
2. **Check Event Postbacks**: Make sure that the in-app event postbacks are enabled and correctly mapped to NewsBreak event types. Verify that values & revenue are included if toggled on.
3. **Review Conversion Data Settings**: For iOS, ensure that the advanced policy is deactivated so NewsBreak can receive all conversion data.
4. **Contact Support**: If everything seems correct but you still don't see any data, it might be helpful to contact NewsBreak support for further assistance.
For more detailed instructions, you can refer to this article: [Introduction to App Install Events](https://help.newsbreak.com/hc/en-us/articles/26530008151309-Introduction-to-App-Install-Events).
